1
00:00:02,878 --> 00:00:06,996
<i>A SHOCHIKU production</i>

2
00:00:12,958 --> 00:00:19,033
<i>WOMEN OF THE NIGHT</i>

3
00:00:47,038 --> 00:00:50,075
<i>Script: Y. YODA
Photography: K. SUGIYAMA</i>

4
00:00:50,998 --> 00:00:54,070
<i>With: Kinuyo TANAKA...
Sanae TAKASUGI</i>

5
00:01:20,918 --> 00:01:23,034
<i>Tomie TSUNODA...
Mitsuo NAGATA</i>

6
00:01:26,998 --> 00:01:33,915
<i>Directed by Kenji MIZOGUCHI</i>

7
00:01:46,918 --> 00:01:49,113
<i>THE POLICE WILL ARREST WOMEN</i>

8
00:01:49,958 --> 00:01:53,075
<i>WHO ARE OUT AT NIGHT.</i>

9
00:02:07,078 --> 00:02:10,957
It's so cold.
No news from your husband?

10
00:02:11,998 --> 00:02:15,035
Your parents and your sister
are in Korea?

11
00:02:15,918 --> 00:02:19,069
They must be back by now.

12
00:02:19,878 --> 00:02:23,917
They don't know my new address.

13
00:02:23,998 --> 00:02:25,875
It's a shame.

14
00:02:25,958 --> 00:02:29,917
There's nobody to protect you.

15
00:02:30,918 --> 00:02:34,069
And my son suffers from tuberculosis.

16
00:02:36,038 --> 00:02:38,950
I'm in a big mess.

17
00:02:39,958 --> 00:02:42,995
I want to sell all this.

18
00:02:44,878 --> 00:02:46,948
Summer clothes.

19
00:02:47,918 --> 00:02:50,876
It's not worth much.

20
00:02:56,118 --> 00:02:58,916
I'll take them for 600 yen.

21
00:02:58,998 --> 00:03:01,034
A little more, please.

22
00:03:01,918 --> 00:03:03,909
It's already too much,

23
00:03:03,998 --> 00:03:06,068
summer clothes are hard to sell.

24
00:03:06,918 --> 00:03:09,113
Business isn't getting any better.

25
00:03:09,998 --> 00:03:13,035
Taxes are increasing.

26
00:03:13,078 --> 00:03:16,866
I'll soon have to hang myself
with those old clothes.

27
00:03:16,958 --> 00:03:19,870
Give me another 50 yen.

28
00:03:19,998 --> 00:03:20,987
No way!

29
00:03:21,078 --> 00:03:22,955
Help me.

30
00:03:23,038 --> 00:03:26,997
Just to buy eggs
for the little one.

31
00:03:27,918 --> 00:03:32,992
Try somewhere else.
You won't get more.

32
00:03:33,998 --> 00:03:35,033
Here, 600 yen.

33
00:03:38,078 --> 00:03:41,070
I have a proposition

34
00:03:41,918 --> 00:03:45,991
if you want to make some money.

35
00:03:46,118 --> 00:03:48,916
What proposition?

36
00:03:49,078 --> 00:03:53,993
A well paid job.

37
00:03:54,078 --> 00:03:59,869
I'd do anything.

38
00:04:00,078 --> 00:04:03,912
There are people
with a lot of money.

39
00:04:04,118 --> 00:04:07,030
I could introduce you to them.

40
00:04:07,918 --> 00:04:09,033
Will I earn some money?

41
00:04:09,118 --> 00:04:12,076
It depends on you.

42
00:04:12,918 --> 00:04:15,068
You can bewitch them.

43
00:04:17,918 --> 00:04:19,033
Don't make fun of me.

44
00:04:19,078 --> 00:04:22,991
It's not much.
Many women do it.

45
00:04:23,118 --> 00:04:26,906
Don't propose this kind of things
to everybody...

46
00:05:03,078 --> 00:05:05,911
How much did she give you?

47
00:05:06,078 --> 00:05:07,875
600 yen.

48
00:05:08,078 --> 00:05:09,955
It's not much.

49
00:05:20,998 --> 00:05:22,989
You're mad at me.

50
00:05:23,958 --> 00:05:26,028
I'd help you if I could.

51
00:05:26,998 --> 00:05:30,070
But I don't earn enough money.

52
00:05:30,958 --> 00:05:34,951
That's enough. I'll manage on my
own for the little one.

53
00:05:37,878 --> 00:05:39,072
I bought you some apples.

54
00:05:40,918 --> 00:05:44,991
I'll grate them.
I have eggs too.

55
00:05:46,078 --> 00:05:49,866
It's your son,
you must take care of him.

56
00:05:53,078 --> 00:05:57,993
You're blaming me
for drinking too much.

57
00:05:58,958 --> 00:06:02,951
The house was burned when
I came back from war.

58
00:06:04,998 --> 00:06:09,116
I'm moonlighting,
I can get caught.

59
00:06:09,958 --> 00:06:11,027
Despite that...

60
00:06:15,998 --> 00:06:18,114
I still bring 6000 yen a month.

61
00:06:19,078 --> 00:06:21,034
It's great.

62
00:06:21,878 --> 00:06:25,996
Tuberculosis isn't so bad.
No need for so many injections.

63
00:06:26,118 --> 00:06:30,111
The doctor pushes you to spend money.

64
00:06:30,918 --> 00:06:31,987
It's not true.

65
00:06:32,118 --> 00:06:33,107
They all do that.

66
00:06:33,958 --> 00:06:35,107
We had an X-ray taken.

67
00:06:35,998 --> 00:06:38,034
If anything happens to the baby

68
00:06:38,118 --> 00:06:41,997
my husband will never forgive me.

69
00:06:49,078 --> 00:06:53,868
Any news from my brother?
Is he still alive?

70
00:06:53,998 --> 00:06:55,909
May he come back soon!

71
00:07:06,918 --> 00:07:09,113
Your brother-in-law does his best.
Forgive him.

72
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:12,074
I know.

73
00:07:13,118 --> 00:07:15,074
If the baby was fine

74
00:07:15,878 --> 00:07:20,030
I could work somewhere.

75
00:07:20,918 --> 00:07:22,067
Let's stop talking about it.

76
00:07:35,998 --> 00:07:37,954
Did you listen to the radio?

77
00:07:38,038 --> 00:07:40,029
We don't have one.

78
00:07:40,118 --> 00:07:42,074
They talked about your husband.

79
00:07:43,038 --> 00:07:43,993
My husband?

80
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:46,994
I was listening to the radio earlier.

81
00:07:47,078 --> 00:07:51,913
I heard:
"Kensaku Owada's family

82
00:07:52,038 --> 00:07:54,950
"must contact Mr. Hirata

83
00:07:55,078 --> 00:07:59,913
about their son. "

84
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:03,995
Thank you for telling us.

85
00:08:06,918 --> 00:08:08,909
Let's go see him now.

86
00:08:09,118 --> 00:08:12,906
Kumiko, can you look after the baby?

87
00:08:13,998 --> 00:08:15,909
I hope he'll be well.

88
00:08:21,958 --> 00:08:25,030
He was so sick at the hospital.

89
00:08:26,998 --> 00:08:30,991
He regretted dying after
so many efforts to survive.

90
00:08:43,118 --> 00:08:44,915
This way.

91
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:18,076
I' really sorry to tell you
these sad news.

92
00:09:19,078 --> 00:09:20,989
Excuse us.

93
00:09:27,918 --> 00:09:29,988
- What's going on?
- It's the parents.

94
00:09:30,918 --> 00:09:31,873
Good.

95
00:09:32,918 --> 00:09:33,987
It's my boss.

96
00:09:41,918 --> 00:09:43,909
We're sorry to bother you.

97
00:09:44,118 --> 00:09:46,074
It must be disheartening.

98
00:09:47,078 --> 00:09:48,067
Sorry.

99
00:09:51,998 --> 00:09:53,113
We're...

100
00:09:54,918 --> 00:09:57,876
deeply affected by this misfortune.

101
00:09:59,878 --> 00:10:02,915
You can come and see me if
you have any problem.

102
00:10:03,918 --> 00:10:04,953
Take heart!

103
00:10:07,958 --> 00:10:09,107
Thank you.

104
00:10:38,878 --> 00:10:41,995
My brother is dead.

105
00:10:44,118 --> 00:10:47,076
Our last hope is gone.

106
00:10:48,958 --> 00:10:50,869
Don't think about it, mom.

107
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:54,028
We have to take care of the funeral.

108
00:11:21,118 --> 00:11:26,067
Mom, he's suffocating. Look.

109
00:11:26,998 --> 00:11:28,067
What's going on?

110
00:11:28,998 --> 00:11:30,875
I'll get the doctor.

111
00:11:30,958 --> 00:11:33,108
Please.

112
00:11:35,958 --> 00:11:38,028
Hurry!

113
00:12:10,038 --> 00:12:11,073
It's time.

114
00:12:13,918 --> 00:12:14,953
I'm leaving.

115
00:12:17,998 --> 00:12:20,068
Fusako!

116
00:12:21,078 --> 00:12:23,990
Here, Natsuko!

117
00:12:25,998 --> 00:12:27,067
Sister!

118
00:12:29,918 --> 00:12:33,069
Finally!
I've been looking for you everywhere.

119
00:12:35,998 --> 00:12:38,990
You're very stylish.

120
00:12:41,958 --> 00:12:44,028
I'm glad.

121
00:12:45,038 --> 00:12:48,997
It's Kumiko from Owada.

122
00:12:49,998 --> 00:12:51,113
You're a big girl!

123
00:12:52,038 --> 00:12:56,077
Do you remember, Kumiko?
She's my sister who was in Korea.

124
00:12:56,998 --> 00:13:00,035
You changed a lot.
I didn't recognize you.

125
00:13:01,078 --> 00:13:03,034
When did you come back?

126
00:13:03,118 --> 00:13:07,873
In september 45.
Your house had burned.

127
00:13:08,078 --> 00:13:12,037
Nobody could tell me
where you were.

128
00:13:13,118 --> 00:13:17,111
How are our parents doing?

129
00:13:18,958 --> 00:13:23,076
Are they fine?

130
00:13:25,118 --> 00:13:26,995
They're dead.

131
00:13:27,078 --> 00:13:28,067
Dead?

132
00:13:30,998 --> 00:13:32,954
Mother died in Korea.

133
00:13:33,958 --> 00:13:36,916
Father came back with me.

134
00:13:38,078 --> 00:13:39,989
Malnutrition.

135
00:13:46,118 --> 00:13:50,077
It has been very hard. Painful.

136
00:13:55,038 --> 00:13:59,111
I lost my husband and my child.

137
00:14:01,998 --> 00:14:02,987
Your husband too!

138
00:14:10,038 --> 00:14:12,074
What are you doing now?

139
00:14:14,038 --> 00:14:14,993
I'm a dancer.

140
00:14:15,078 --> 00:14:16,875
It's great.

141
00:14:18,118 --> 00:14:19,107
And you?

142
00:14:19,918 --> 00:14:24,036
I didn't want to cause my
husband's family anymore troubles.

143
00:14:24,918 --> 00:14:27,990
So I left them and I'm working

144
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:30,914
in a company.

145
00:14:31,998 --> 00:14:34,068
She's an executive secretary.

146
00:14:34,918 --> 00:14:37,034
I'd like to leave the factory

147
00:14:38,038 --> 00:14:41,110
to work somewhere else.

148
00:14:41,958 --> 00:14:43,107
Where do you live?

149
00:14:43,918 --> 00:14:45,988
In a flat near Tengejaya.

150
00:14:46,918 --> 00:14:48,988
Can I live with you?

151
00:14:49,918 --> 00:14:54,116
I'm living with friends.
We're four in one room.

152
00:15:01,918 --> 00:15:05,957
We never thought we would
meet like that.

153
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:09,913
It's true.

154
00:15:09,998 --> 00:15:12,990
But you, you're still luckier.

155
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,033
Why?

156
00:15:14,118 --> 00:15:16,109
You had a happy youth.

157
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:18,107
You were married.

158
00:15:18,998 --> 00:15:20,989
We, the youth,

159
00:15:21,078 --> 00:15:23,069
won't be able to be happy anymore.

160
00:15:23,118 --> 00:15:25,916
It's necessarily true.

161
00:15:27,118 --> 00:15:30,076
Your clothes are very nice.
Where do they come from?

162
00:15:31,038 --> 00:15:32,915
I had them made here.

163
00:15:32,998 --> 00:15:35,910
It must be expensive.

164
00:15:36,078 --> 00:15:37,067
Very.

165
00:15:37,918 --> 00:15:41,069
I haven't finished
paying for them yet.

166
00:15:41,998 --> 00:15:43,954
What if I became a dancer?

167
00:15:44,038 --> 00:15:45,994
Don't be ridiculous.

168
00:15:51,078 --> 00:15:52,909
Welcome.

169
00:15:54,038 --> 00:15:54,993
A visit?

170
00:15:55,078 --> 00:15:56,067
Come in.

171
00:15:57,918 --> 00:15:59,909
He's our boss.

172
00:16:00,078 --> 00:16:03,036
She's my sister I was looking for.

173
00:16:03,918 --> 00:16:05,954
We met by chance.

174
00:16:06,038 --> 00:16:08,916
Like in a dream.

175
00:16:08,998 --> 00:16:11,068
I'm happy for you.

176
00:16:11,918 --> 00:16:14,955
Your sister talked to me about you.
I was worried.

177
00:16:15,038 --> 00:16:16,073
Thank you.

178
00:16:16,118 --> 00:16:19,030
It must have been hard.

179
00:17:11,118 --> 00:17:13,951
If only I could dance...

180
00:17:15,078 --> 00:17:17,990
My clothes aren't so nice.

181
00:17:21,038 --> 00:17:22,073
It's time to go back.

182
00:17:22,918 --> 00:17:24,954
I want to stay.

183
00:17:25,078 --> 00:17:28,115
Your mother won't be happy
if you come back late.

184
00:17:29,038 --> 00:17:31,871
It's wonderful.

185
00:17:47,118 --> 00:17:48,870
Hello.

186
00:18:07,038 --> 00:18:10,917
Don't use my cosmetics.

187
00:18:11,038 --> 00:18:12,949
Skinflint!

188
00:18:12,998 --> 00:18:16,957
Skinflint yourself!
Why don't you buy some?

189
00:18:17,958 --> 00:18:20,916
I need of this to work.

190
00:18:20,998 --> 00:18:22,954
I don't earn a lot of money.

191
00:18:23,038 --> 00:18:26,951
You?
An executive secretary?

192
00:18:28,918 --> 00:18:33,867
Do you have another
contract with him?

193
00:18:34,118 --> 00:18:36,109
Don't be ridiculous.

194
00:18:37,118 --> 00:18:40,952
You should take advantage of it.

195
00:18:41,918 --> 00:18:43,954
It's not my boss' type.

196
00:19:07,118 --> 00:19:11,987
The boat arrives tonight.

197
00:19:12,998 --> 00:19:15,910
We must prepare 3 million.

198
00:19:16,038 --> 00:19:18,996
I'm counting on you.

199
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:38,869
We'll get caught.

200
00:19:39,918 --> 00:19:41,909
You're my secretary.

201
00:19:43,998 --> 00:19:44,908
Sir!

202
00:19:45,038 --> 00:19:46,994
Do you want me to buy you something?

203
00:19:47,078 --> 00:19:51,993
Do you really care about me?

204
00:19:52,078 --> 00:19:53,955
Of course.

205
00:19:54,118 --> 00:19:55,107
Is it true?

206
00:19:55,918 --> 00:19:57,874
What question!

207
00:19:58,118 --> 00:20:00,951
I'm worried.

208
00:20:01,038 --> 00:20:02,869
It's useless.

209
00:20:02,958 --> 00:20:05,916
I'm treating you well.
What else do you want?

210
00:20:09,038 --> 00:20:11,996
I'll be even nicer.

211
00:20:38,118 --> 00:20:39,870
Miss!

212
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:41,949
Where is the director?

213
00:20:42,118 --> 00:20:44,029
I don't know.

214
00:20:44,118 --> 00:20:47,110
- It worries me.
- Why?

215
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,994
I just got a phone call.

216
00:20:50,918 --> 00:20:52,067
The police is coming.

217
00:20:52,878 --> 00:20:54,914
- What?
- A search!

218
00:20:55,958 --> 00:20:56,947
Damn!

219
00:21:11,038 --> 00:21:14,030
We must not keep that here.

220
00:21:14,878 --> 00:21:15,947
I have to stay here.

221
00:21:16,038 --> 00:21:18,916
What do you want to do?
Can I help you?

222
00:21:19,038 --> 00:21:22,030
Can you hide it somewhere?

223
00:21:22,878 --> 00:21:24,027
I'll take it home.

224
00:21:24,918 --> 00:21:25,953
Thansk a lot.

225
00:21:26,918 --> 00:21:27,907
It's heavy.

226
00:21:28,038 --> 00:21:29,107
I'll manage.

227
00:21:43,998 --> 00:21:45,067
Miss,

228
00:21:45,918 --> 00:21:47,033
Your coat is trailing on the ground.

229
00:22:39,118 --> 00:22:42,076
Did Natsuko go out?

230
00:22:42,118 --> 00:22:44,916
No, she should be here.

231
00:22:49,958 --> 00:22:51,994
Open! Quick!

232
00:22:57,918 --> 00:22:59,954
You? At this hour?

233
00:23:02,958 --> 00:23:04,914
What's going on?

234
00:23:06,038 --> 00:23:07,994
There's a police search.

235
00:23:08,118 --> 00:23:11,110
I took it to hide it.

236
00:23:13,958 --> 00:23:15,073
Put it somewhere.

237
00:23:20,038 --> 00:23:21,949
Take care of it.

238
00:23:49,918 --> 00:23:51,988
What were you doing, Natsuko?

239
00:23:52,118 --> 00:23:53,995
Nothing special.

240
00:23:54,078 --> 00:23:58,071
Don't lie.
Watch what you're doing.

241
00:24:00,958 --> 00:24:05,110
I must take care of you
without her parents.

242
00:24:05,958 --> 00:24:08,995
You know it very well.

243
00:24:09,918 --> 00:24:15,868
Some men took advantage
of me on the boat.

244
00:24:20,998 --> 00:24:23,068
I often considered killing myself.

245
00:24:26,118 --> 00:24:30,031
It's the hope of living happily
here that stopped me.

246
00:24:31,878 --> 00:24:34,950
It would have been better
if I had been sold.

247
00:24:43,038 --> 00:24:45,029
I could be his mistress.

248
00:24:45,878 --> 00:24:47,072
The director talked to you?

249
00:24:47,918 --> 00:24:52,036
Yes. I'm not a kid anymore,
I can do whatever I want.

250
00:24:56,118 --> 00:24:59,030
Think carefully.

251
00:25:00,918 --> 00:25:01,987
Leave me alone.

252
00:26:05,918 --> 00:26:07,874
Hello.

253
00:26:10,918 --> 00:26:13,034
I was wondering how you were doing.

254
00:26:14,918 --> 00:26:16,954
Did your husband come back?

255
00:26:18,038 --> 00:26:19,073
Unfortunately, no.

256
00:26:19,918 --> 00:26:20,987
I'm sorry.

257
00:26:21,078 --> 00:26:23,956
I'm free to do whatever I want.

258
00:26:29,078 --> 00:26:33,071
It's about what you proposed me.

259
00:26:34,118 --> 00:26:35,995
Are you ready?

260
00:26:52,118 --> 00:26:54,996
She's still not back yet?

261
00:27:00,958 --> 00:27:05,076
I'll check at Owada's.
Maybe she's still there.

262
00:27:07,038 --> 00:27:08,915
Where is she hiding?

263
00:27:16,078 --> 00:27:19,991
You never had sex with my sister?

264
00:27:20,958 --> 00:27:23,870
No, never.

265
00:27:24,998 --> 00:27:27,034
So why did she run away?

266
00:27:27,118 --> 00:27:29,109
I don't know.

267
00:27:39,078 --> 00:27:41,069
Maybe it's her.

268
00:27:41,958 --> 00:27:43,027
Hello.

269
00:27:45,918 --> 00:27:48,113
I wanted to check your place.
Is my sister here?

270
00:27:48,958 --> 00:27:50,027
No.

271
00:27:50,958 --> 00:27:52,073
Didn't she come?

272
00:27:52,918 --> 00:27:54,874
What's happening to her?

273
00:27:55,998 --> 00:27:58,876
She doesn't come back home lately.

274
00:28:01,918 --> 00:28:03,067
How do you do?

275
00:28:03,918 --> 00:28:05,067
Make yourself comfortable.

276
00:28:08,918 --> 00:28:09,953
Good bye.

277
00:28:14,998 --> 00:28:17,034
What's going on, Kumiko?

278
